        <bioghist>
            <p>Robert Joki, author of Saratoga Lost, collected various items related to Saratoga in the course of his historical research. A large portion of the 19th century stereoviews that were used in writing Saratoga Lost, as well as a collection of printed guides, documents, advertisements, and ephemera relating to Saratoga Springs have been acquired by the library.</p>
